The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 HCL net profit at Rs 136 cr

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 Nadar: Looking ahead

 New Delhi, Aug. 19: Shiv Nadar-owned HCL Technologies Ltds net profit in the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 136.45 crore against Rs 85.22 crore a year ago. The companys consolidated net profit in the fourth quarter was Rs 233 crore.

 HCLs revenues for the quarter ended June 30 was Rs 1,253.8 crore. The board has recommended a final dividend of Rs 4 per share, or 200 per cent per share with face value of Rs 2, for the year ended June 30, which takes the full-year dividend to 800 per cent.

 The companys total income was Rs 813.18 crore in the fourth quarter of 2005-06 compared with Rs 424.09 crore in the year-ago period.

 The company reported a net profit of Rs 638.38 crore for 2005-06 compared with Rs 329.27 crore a year ago. Total income was Rs 3,116.26 crore against Rs 1,530.03 crore a year ago.

 HCL has benefited from contracts including those from Hemel Hempstead, UK-based DSG International and San Rafael, California-based Autodesk Inc, whose design software is used in architecture, engineering and movie making, to provide services ranging from writing software codes to management of infrastructure.

 Emerging high growth areas such as remote infrastructure management, where we have virtually created a new market space through our co-sourcing model, has been a key growth driver, said Vineet Nayar, president of HCL. 




